   - AI Token Efficiency: The system currently passes the entire text of up to 5 documents to the summarize endpoint. As the "Life Dump" grows, we will hit token limits or incur high costs.
       - Solution: Implement a sliding window or "Map-Reduce" pattern for document summarization before the final synthesis.
   - Concurrency: Node.js is single-threaded. Multiple users running "Blender" syntheses simultaneously will block the event loop. We should offload AI processing to a Worker Thread or a separate task queue (like BullMQ) as we scale to users.

